    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T15:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T15:45:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>155. Telegram From the Commander of Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="from">Clark</persName>) to the Commander in Chief,
                    Atlantic (<persName corresp="#p_DARL1" type="to">Dennison</persName>)<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d155fn0">Source: Naval Historical Center, Area Files,
                        Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Operational Immediate; Exclusive. Repeated
                        to <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_COMCARIBSEAFRON1"
                            >COMCARIBSEAFRON</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_COMKWESTFOR1"
                            >COMKWESTFOR</gloss>, and COMNAVBASE <gloss target="#t_GTMO1"
                            >GTMO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">Essex</hi>, Caribbean</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1961-04-19T15:45:00">April 19, 1961, 3:45
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192045Z. Exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gray</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SBK1"
                        >Smith</persName>, OʼDonnell, McElroy from <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                        >Clark</persName>. Bumpy Road.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Final report from CTU 81.8.3 “saw nothing to indicate any chance of
                        evacuation. Beach appears completely held by light <persName
                            corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> forces.”</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>My destroyers are clear of beach and rejoining <gloss target="#t_CEF1"
                            >CEF</gloss> ships.<note n="1" xml:id="d155fn1">At 3:20, <persName
                                corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> reported: “CTU 81.8.3 straddled
                            by shore battery. Ordered withdrawal full speed.” (<gloss
                                target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8 telegram 192020Z to <gloss
                                target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss>, April 19;
                            ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
